# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: AlfredArc | Scene: GallowCreek1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah let the shivers pass over and through her."
    new "Sarah let the shivers pass over and through her."

    old "Then she continued walking."
    new "Then she continued walking."

    old "She didn't know what had just happened, nor did she intend to find out."
    new "She didn't know what had just happened, nor did she intend to find out."

    old "She had come here to be safe. Safe from all the madness out there."
    new "She had come here to be safe. Safe from all the madness out there."

    old "The last thing she was looking for was strange voices speaking to her."
    new "The last thing she was looking for was strange voices speaking to her."

    old "Looking back as she walked, she waved towards Sigmund and the others, who each waved back."
    new "Looking back as she walked, she waved towards Sigmund and the others, who each waved back."

    old "She saw their cart pull out, continuing their journey."
    new "She saw their cart pull out, continuing their journey."

    old "Just as Sigmund had promised her, Gallow's Creek was no more than a few minutes up the road, and soon Sarah found herself coming upon the village."
    new "Just as Sigmund had promised her, Gallow's Creek was no more than a few minutes up the road, and soon Sarah found herself coming upon the village."

    old "The road was little more than a trodden path, stomped into existence by the passing of men and horses."
    new "The road was little more than a trodden path, stomped into existence by the passing of men and horses."

    old "She was flanked on either side by vast fields of golden wheat."
    new "She was flanked on either side by vast fields of golden wheat."

    old "Slowly, the setting sun was casting a golden light over the land, making it almost hard to look at."
    new "Slowly, the setting sun was casting a golden light over the land, making it almost hard to look at."

    old "In the midsts of the fields, people hard at work. So far away, they seemed like specks."
    new "In the midsts of the fields, people hard at work. So far away, they seemed like specks."

    old "Sarah walked in awe."
    new "Sarah walked in awe."

    old "Growing up, she had seen the lands around the Capital in Rosanna, but she had never truly seen those fields from so close."
    new "Growing up, she had seen the lands around the Capital in Rosanna, but she had never truly seen those fields from so close."

    old "Now, walking among them, the sensations were almost overpowering."
    new "Now, walking among them, the sensations were almost overpowering."

    old "The way the fields reached all the way to the horizon, made them feel more like an ocean."
    new "The way the fields reached all the way to the horizon, made them feel more like an ocean."

    old "As she continued to walk, Sarah realized more than a few of the people in the field were taking notice of her."
    new "As she continued to walk, Sarah realized more than a few of the people in the field were taking notice of her."

    old "Gallow Creek was a tiny hovel from what Sigmund had told her."
    new "Gallow Creek was a tiny hovel from what Sigmund had told her."

    old "Safe and full of good people from what he said, but they probably were not used to many visitors."
    new "Safe and full of good people from what he said, but they probably were not used to many visitors."

    old "Sarah continued to walk until she came upon a small collection of buildings."
    new "Sarah continued to walk until she came upon a small collection of buildings."

    old "None were too impressive, but gathered around a makeshift square, she assumed this was what had to pass for the center of the town."
    new "None were too impressive, but gathered around a makeshift square, she assumed this was what had to pass for the center of the town."

    old "Much like the road that lead to Gallow Creek, it wasn't so much made as formed naturally."
    new "Much like the road that lead to Gallow Creek, it wasn't so much made as formed naturally."

    old "Just as she was taking it all in, she heard a voice."
    new "Just as she was taking it all in, she heard a voice."

    old "Voice\" \"Oy!"
    new "Voice\" \"Oy!"

    old "Sarah turned, startled."
    new "Sarah turned, startled."

    old "A young man, close to her in age, was climbing down from a cart."
    new "A young man, close to her in age, was climbing down from a cart."

    old "Young man\" \"Who are you, exactly?"
    new "Young man\" \"Who are you, exactly?"

    old "He came closer to her as he spoke."
    new "He came closer to her as he spoke."

    old "Hey there, my name is Sarah, uhm...is this Gallow's Creek?"
    new "Hey there, my name is Sarah, uhm...is this Gallow's Creek?"

    old "Young man\" \"Ay, that it is. But what business is that of yours?"
    new "Young man\" \"Ay, that it is. But what business is that of yours?"

    old "He regarded her with more than a little suspicion."
    new "He regarded her with more than a little suspicion."

    old "Well...uhm...this might sound odd but I was brought here by a man named Sigmund."
    new "Well...uhm...this might sound odd but I was brought here by a man named Sigmund."

    old "Young man\" \"Sigmund? Ay, I know him. He send you?"
    new "Young man\" \"Sigmund? Ay, I know him. He send you?"

    old "Yes, in a way."
    new "Yes, in a way."

    old "This is all...difficult to explain, but he said that this place was a good place, with good people."
    new "This is all...difficult to explain, but he said that this place was a good place, with good people."

    old "And that if I needed shelter, I could find it here. That's why I came."
    new "And that if I needed shelter, I could find it here. That's why I came."

    old "The young man frowned, regarding her a moment longer."
    new "The young man frowned, regarding her a moment longer."

    old "Young man\" \"I don't know about good people, but this here town is a decent play to live, ay. Decent as any, I imagine."
    new "Young man\" \"I don't know about good people, but this here town is a decent play to live, ay. Decent as any, I imagine."

    old "Young man\" \"And I suppose if Sigmund liked ya, you can't be too shady."
    new "Young man\" \"And I suppose if Sigmund liked ya, you can't be too shady."

    old "Shady?"
    new "Shady?"

    old "Sarah couldn't help but feel a bit outraged that anyone could think of her as such."
    new "Sarah couldn't help but feel a bit outraged that anyone could think of her as such."

    old "The young man smiled."
    new "The young man smiled."

    old "Young man\" \"Sorry, this town don't get many visitors. And those that do rarely look like...well, you."
    new "Young man\" \"Sorry, this town don't get many visitors. And those that do rarely look like...well, you."

    old "He gestured at her with his head as if that was supposed to mean something."
    new "He gestured at her with his head as if that was supposed to mean something."

    old "He extended a hand and Sarah took it."
    new "He extended a hand and Sarah took it."

    old "The name's Marius, by the way."
    new "The name's Marius, by the way."

    old "Nice to meet you, Marius."
    new "Nice to meet you, Marius."

    old "Nice to meet you as well, Sarah was it?"
    new "Nice to meet you as well, Sarah was it?"

    old "Well, luck's on your side I suppose, you came here just the right time."
    new "Well, luck's on your side I suppose, you came here just the right time."

    old "Harvest season has only just begun. Ain't never got enough hands for all the work that need be doing."
    new "Harvest season has only just begun. Ain't never got enough hands for all the work that need be doing."

    old "Really? That's great! If I can have shelter here, I'll be sure to do my part."
    new "Really? That's great! If I can have shelter here, I'll be sure to do my part."

    old "Though, I don't know too much about farming..."
    new "Though, I don't know too much about farming..."

    old "She thought it better to be honest."
    new "She thought it better to be honest."

    old "Marius smiled."
    new "Marius smiled."

    old "Yeah, I didn't take you for much of a farmer, wearin that fancy dress of yours."
    new "Yeah, I didn't take you for much of a farmer, wearin that fancy dress of yours."

    old "Sarah felt a blush on her face at his compliment."
    new "Sarah felt a blush on her face at his compliment."

    old "Still, plenty of other work to be done. Basket weavin for takin in the harvest, feedin animals, all that sort of work. Some cookin too."
    new "Still, plenty of other work to be done. Basket weavin for takin in the harvest, feedin animals, all that sort of work. Some cookin too."

    old "Sarah nodded along. She didn't know how to do any of that, but she was eager to learn or at least try."
    new "Sarah nodded along. She didn't know how to do any of that, but she was eager to learn or at least try."

    old "Also, she knew she wasn't in much of a position to refuse. She needed shelter, and in a place like this, that meant you had to work for it."
    new "Also, she knew she wasn't in much of a position to refuse. She needed shelter, and in a place like this, that meant you had to work for it."

    old "I got a place you can stay at. As good as any house you'll find here in town. Then we can see about you gettin a job."
    new "I got a place you can stay at. As good as any house you'll find here in town. Then we can see about you gettin a job."

    old "Really? You'd do that for me?"
    new "Really? You'd do that for me?"

    old "Ay, why not."
    new "Ay, why not."

    old "We might not have all too much here, but that never meant we turn down a stranger in need."
    new "We might not have all too much here, but that never meant we turn down a stranger in need."

    old "Thank you so much!"
    new "Thank you so much!"

    old "Sarah almost wanted to hug him, but restrained herself."
    new "Sarah almost wanted to hug him, but restrained herself."

    old "Follow along then."
    new "Follow along then."

    old "Marius began to walk and Sarah quickly paced along side of him."
    new "Marius began to walk and Sarah quickly paced along side of him."

    old "He walked in broad steps, clearly a man that was always on the move. For every step of his, she had to take nearly two."
    new "He walked in broad steps, clearly a man that was always on the move. For every step of his, she had to take nearly two."

    old "That over there was the town square, but you might a figured that out."
    new "That over there was the town square, but you might a figured that out."

    old "We gather there for important decisions, or when we have a festival, that sort of thing."
    new "We gather there for important decisions, or when we have a festival, that sort of thing."

    old "Marius pointed into the distance."
    new "Marius pointed into the distance."

    old "Them fields are up first in the harvest season, then we all work together and go about a circle, till we bring in all the crops."
    new "Them fields are up first in the harvest season, then we all work together and go about a circle, till we bring in all the crops."

    old "Takes a good few weeks or so."
    new "Takes a good few weeks or so."

    old "He pointed towards another direction. A few small houses dotted the distance."
    new "He pointed towards another direction. A few small houses dotted the distance."

    old "Some families over there, and in the other direction couple more."
    new "Some families over there, and in the other direction couple more."

    old "All in all, I figure we got some forty families that live up here in town."
    new "All in all, I figure we got some forty families that live up here in town."

    old "Sarah listend intently as Marius explained the workings of Gallow Creek."
    new "Sarah listend intently as Marius explained the workings of Gallow Creek."

    old "She realized fewer people lived in this town then maybe a single street in the Capital of Rosanna."
    new "She realized fewer people lived in this town then maybe a single street in the Capital of Rosanna."

    old "But maybe that was a good thing, she thought to herself."
    new "But maybe that was a good thing, she thought to herself."

    old "In the city, everyone was a stranger to everyone else. Here, people might actually know one another."
    new "In the city, everyone was a stranger to everyone else. Here, people might actually know one another."

    old "Marius walked off the road, into one of the fields and pointed out a nearby stone house."
    new "Marius walked off the road, into one of the fields and pointed out a nearby stone house."

    old "That's my home, right over there."
    new "That's my home, right over there."

    old "Sarah smiled as she saw it. It seemed almost the perfect image of a small cottage."
    new "Sarah smiled as she saw it. It seemed almost the perfect image of a small cottage."

    old "Far from the castle she had grown up in, but all the more appealing for it."
    new "Far from the castle she had grown up in, but all the more appealing for it."

    old "It looks amazing."
    new "It looks amazing."

    old "Marius laughed."
    new "Marius laughed."

    old "No need to butter me up. I know it ain't much, but it's home."
    new "No need to butter me up. I know it ain't much, but it's home."

    old "Sarah observed Marius as she followed him."
    new "Sarah observed Marius as she followed him."

    old "Growing up at court, her father had taught her from an early age to learn to read people's faces."
    new "Growing up at court, her father had taught her from an early age to learn to read people's faces."

    old "What they pretended to think. What they were really thinking. Lies. Pretend. Hidden meanings."
    new "What they pretended to think. What they were really thinking. Lies. Pretend. Hidden meanings."

    old "But when she searched Marius' face, she found nothing of the sort."
    new "But when she searched Marius' face, she found nothing of the sort."

    old "In his face, there were no secret worlds or hidden designs."
    new "In his face, there were no secret worlds or hidden designs."

    old "He simply seemed happy and kind."
    new "He simply seemed happy and kind."

    old "She envied him for it."
    new "She envied him for it."

    old "The wooden door to the house swung open with a loud creaking noise, its hinges more than rusted."
    new "The wooden door to the house swung open with a loud creaking noise, its hinges more than rusted."

    old "Stepping through, the air cooled noticeably."
    new "Stepping through, the air cooled noticeably."

    old "Sarah looked around and saw that it was a good deal less charming on the inside than it had been from the outside."
    new "Sarah looked around and saw that it was a good deal less charming on the inside than it had been from the outside."

    old "Small, cramped, and oddly cluttered."
    new "Small, cramped, and oddly cluttered."

    old "Sorry if it's a bit of a mess. I been meaning to clean up for a while now, but...you know, harvest season."
    new "Sorry if it's a bit of a mess. I been meaning to clean up for a while now, but...you know, harvest season."

    old "He shrugged as if that was plenty of explanation."
    new "He shrugged as if that was plenty of explanation."

    old "No, don't worry...it's perfect."
    new "No, don't worry...it's perfect."

    old "Suddenly, another voice called out."
    new "Suddenly, another voice called out."

    old "Voice\" \"Who is that?"
    new "Voice\" \"Who is that?"

    old "Voice\" \"That you, Marius?"
    new "Voice\" \"That you, Marius?"

    old "No worries, just me dad!"
    new "No worries, just me dad!"

    old "Marius turned to Sarah."
    new "Marius turned to Sarah."

    old "Sorry, forgot to mention, I live here with my dad."
    new "Sorry, forgot to mention, I live here with my dad."

    old "Sarah watched as an old man stumbled into the room."
    new "Sarah watched as an old man stumbled into the room."

    old "Somewhere in his sixties, old age and hard work had ridden his body hard."
    new "Somewhere in his sixties, old age and hard work had ridden his body hard."

    old "Though despite that, Sarah could seem the faint resemblance."
    new "Though despite that, Sarah could seem the faint resemblance."

    old "Hello, sir!"
    new "Hello, sir!"

    old "The old man frowned as he saw her."
    new "The old man frowned as he saw her."

    old "Old man\" \"Boy! I told you to warn me when we get visitors. Especially one as lovely as this one."
    new "Old man\" \"Boy! I told you to warn me when we get visitors. Especially one as lovely as this one."

    old "Sarah blushed and smiled."
    new "Sarah blushed and smiled."

    old "Sorry, dad. But it wasn't my fault. She just wandered into town."
    new "Sorry, dad. But it wasn't my fault. She just wandered into town."

    old "The man frowned again."
    new "The man frowned again."

    old "Wonder into town did ya? Well, you can call me Alfred, and I see you already met my boy, Marius."
    new "Wonder into town did ya? Well, you can call me Alfred, and I see you already met my boy, Marius."

    old "He's been very welcoming so far!"
    new "He's been very welcoming so far!"

    old "Alfred laughed. The laugh was somehow charged with meaning, though Sarah could not suss out what it was."
    new "Alfred laughed. The laugh was somehow charged with meaning, though Sarah could not suss out what it was."

    old "Yeah, I bet he has been."
    new "Yeah, I bet he has been."

    old "She's looking for shelter and I promised she could stay here with us."
    new "She's looking for shelter and I promised she could stay here with us."

    old "If that's fine with you, of course, sir."
    new "If that's fine with you, of course, sir."

    old "Sarah watched as the man pondered it for a moment."
    new "Sarah watched as the man pondered it for a moment."

    old "Fine, she can stay."
    new "Fine, she can stay."

    old "But ain't nobody stayin here for nothin."
    new "But ain't nobody stayin here for nothin."

    old "He gestured around."
    new "He gestured around."

    old "Maybe a womanly touch can do this place good. You clean up this mess and do the cook work, you can earn a spot."
    new "Maybe a womanly touch can do this place good. You clean up this mess and do the cook work, you can earn a spot."

    old "Sarah smiled widely."
    new "Sarah smiled widely."

    old "Thank you, sir! I will!"
    new "Thank you, sir! I will!"

    old "It seemed like a small price for a place to stay."
    new "It seemed like a small price for a place to stay."

    old "Just for a while so she wouldn't have to worry about where she'd sleep next. Just a brief moment of rest."
    new "Just for a while so she wouldn't have to worry about where she'd sleep next. Just a brief moment of rest."

    old "Mind yourself though!"
    new "Mind yourself though!"

    old "This place might look like a mess, but I know every knife and fork and what not."
    new "This place might look like a mess, but I know every knife and fork and what not."

    old "If a thing goes missin, you'll be in trouble. And in this town, we don't do no complicated city justice."
    new "If a thing goes missin, you'll be in trouble. And in this town, we don't do no complicated city justice."

    old "Thieves get a lashing and get run out of town."
    new "Thieves get a lashing and get run out of town."

    old "Of course sir, but I'm no thief, I promise!"
    new "Of course sir, but I'm no thief, I promise!"

    old "Best not be."
    new "Best not be."

    old "The man gestured at Marius."
    new "The man gestured at Marius."

    old "Go on now, boy. Get our guest settled and show her the chores."
    new "Go on now, boy. Get our guest settled and show her the chores."

    old "Marius nodded."
    new "Marius nodded."

    old "Of course, sir."
    new "Of course, sir."

    old "With that, the old man stumbled back into the room he came from, clearly exhausted from this little effort."
    new "With that, the old man stumbled back into the room he came from, clearly exhausted from this little effort."

    old "Sorry bout my dad."
    new "Sorry bout my dad."

    old "Oh, no worries. He seems nice."
    new "Oh, no worries. He seems nice."

    old "Marius grinned."
    new "Marius grinned."

    old "He's been cranky for a good few years now. Ever since mom died."
    new "He's been cranky for a good few years now. Ever since mom died."

    old "Sarah saw Marius turn his eyes away from her."
    new "Sarah saw Marius turn his eyes away from her."

    old "Oh, I didn't...I'm sorry."
    new "Oh, I didn't...I'm sorry."

    old "Marius shrugged."
    new "Marius shrugged."

    old "It's fine. Been a while now. You learn to move on."
    new "It's fine. Been a while now. You learn to move on."

    old "I get it."
    new "I get it."

    old "Marius frowned."
    new "Marius frowned."

    old "You do? Why is that?"
    new "You do? Why is that?"

    old "Sarah wondered about how much she wanted to reveal about herself."
    new "Sarah wondered about how much she wanted to reveal about herself."

    old "It's nothing, maybe we can talk about that another time. I, uhh...you're dad told you to show me the chores, right?"
    new "It's nothing, maybe we can talk about that another time. I, uhh...you're dad told you to show me the chores, right?"

    old "Oh, yeah, I almost forgot."
    new "Oh, yeah, I almost forgot."

    old "Marius walked over towards a small alcove that passed for a kitchen."
    new "Marius walked over towards a small alcove that passed for a kitchen."

    old "This here is the stove. Neither me nor my dad can cook to save our lives. So if you could give it a try, that be amazin."
    new "This here is the stove. Neither me nor my dad can cook to save our lives. So if you could give it a try, that be amazin."

    old "Sarah nodded, even though she had never touched a stove in her life."
    new "Sarah nodded, even though she had never touched a stove in her life."

    old "Somehow, by nature of her being a women, they imagined she had a natural affinity for these things."
    new "Somehow, by nature of her being a women, they imagined she had a natural affinity for these things."

    old "Marius gestured at the room."
    new "Marius gestured at the room."

    old "The rest of the house, as you can see, is a mess."
    new "The rest of the house, as you can see, is a mess."

    old "So like my dad said, maybe you can clean it up a bit. You women got better eyes for that sort of stuff, no?"
    new "So like my dad said, maybe you can clean it up a bit. You women got better eyes for that sort of stuff, no?"

    old "Sarah nodded, though she had cleaned about as much in her life as she had cooked."
    new "Sarah nodded, though she had cleaned about as much in her life as she had cooked."

    old "Still, she wasn't about to tell him that she usually had her servants do these tasks."
    new "Still, she wasn't about to tell him that she usually had her servants do these tasks."

    old "Sarah did her best to remember how her servants used to do these tasks."
    new "Sarah did her best to remember how her servants used to do these tasks."

    old "Well...I guess I'll get started then."
    new "Well...I guess I'll get started then."

    old "Wait, hang on a moment."
    new "Wait, hang on a moment."

    old "Marius dissapeared into a different room and then emerged with a dress in hand."
    new "Marius dissapeared into a different room and then emerged with a dress in hand."

    old "I mean, you don't have to...but..."
    new "I mean, you don't have to...but..."

    old "He stuttered a bit, his face averted."
    new "He stuttered a bit, his face averted."

    old "I just figured, your dress is so expensive looking, you probably don't want to get it dirty with cleaning."
    new "I just figured, your dress is so expensive looking, you probably don't want to get it dirty with cleaning."

    old "This is one of my mom's old dresses, but I think it's the same size. Maybe you can use this?"
    new "This is one of my mom's old dresses, but I think it's the same size. Maybe you can use this?"

    old "Sarah smiled as she took the dress."
    new "Sarah smiled as she took the dress."

    old "It was indeed far less in quality than what she was used to, but that made it perfect for cleaning."
    new "It was indeed far less in quality than what she was used to, but that made it perfect for cleaning."

    old "Thank you, I will."
    new "Thank you, I will."

    old "The two stood awkwardly for a moment."
    new "The two stood awkwardly for a moment."

    old "Marius frowned, not understanding."
    new "Marius frowned, not understanding."

    old "A longer pause."
    new "A longer pause."

    old "Is there anywhere for me to get...changed?"
    new "Is there anywhere for me to get...changed?"

    old "Oh!!!"
    new "Oh!!!"

    old "Marius' face suddenly turned bright red."
    new "Marius' face suddenly turned bright red."

    old "Of course, I'm so stupid!"
    new "Of course, I'm so stupid!"

    old "Sarah laughed at his nervous expression."
    new "Sarah laughed at his nervous expression."

    old "It's fine, just any room will do."
    new "It's fine, just any room will do."

    old "Yeah, of course, no problem!"
    new "Yeah, of course, no problem!"

    old "He pointed to a door at the far end of the room."
    new "He pointed to a door at the far end of the room."

    old "That's the storage closet. You can get changed in there."
    new "That's the storage closet. You can get changed in there."

    old "Sarah quickly entered the room, dress in hand."
    new "Sarah quickly entered the room, dress in hand."

    old "The storage closet was hardly big enough for her to properly stand in, but in this house it was as close as she'd get to some privacy."
    new "The storage closet was hardly big enough for her to properly stand in, but in this house it was as close as she'd get to some privacy."

    old "The walls of the room were lined with dried meats and other non-perishing foods."
    new "The walls of the room were lined with dried meats and other non-perishing foods."

    old "A small pile of firewood filled up the corner."
    new "A small pile of firewood filled up the corner."

    old "Winters here would be rough, she imagined."
    new "Winters here would be rough, she imagined."

    old "Slipping out of her dress, Sarah allowed it to fall to the floor."
    new "Slipping out of her dress, Sarah allowed it to fall to the floor."

    old "Kneeling down in her only her underwear, she felt the wind moving through the house."
    new "Kneeling down in her only her underwear, she felt the wind moving through the house."

    old "She carefully folded her dress and stored it on one of the empty shelves."
    new "She carefully folded her dress and stored it on one of the empty shelves."

    old "Her dress was valuable. Maybe the only real thing of value she had left, she realized."
    new "Her dress was valuable. Maybe the only real thing of value she had left, she realized."

    old "It was of no use in this town, but perhaps she could use it in the future. Better to have the option, she thought as she stored it."
    new "It was of no use in this town, but perhaps she could use it in the future. Better to have the option, she thought as she stored it."

    old "Sarah held up the dress of Marius' mother."
    new "Sarah held up the dress of Marius' mother."

    old "Though the material was coarse, she found the design of it quite pretty."
    new "Though the material was coarse, she found the design of it quite pretty."

    old "It was clear that his mother had sewn and adjusted the dress to make it more than it had been."
    new "It was clear that his mother had sewn and adjusted the dress to make it more than it had been."

    old "Sarah lifted it over her head and allowed it to slide down her body."
    new "Sarah lifted it over her head and allowed it to slide down her body."

    old "It fitted easily, she was probably a few sizes thinner, she realized, but not by so much that the dress looked odd on her."
    new "It fitted easily, she was probably a few sizes thinner, she realized, but not by so much that the dress looked odd on her."

    old "As Sarah patted the dress down, trying to get rid of any creases, she studied herself as best she could without a mirror."
    new "As Sarah patted the dress down, trying to get rid of any creases, she studied herself as best she could without a mirror."

    old "It looked nice, she concluded."
    new "It looked nice, she concluded."

    old "Finished, she stepped out of the storage closet, back into the room."
    new "Finished, she stepped out of the storage closet, back into the room."

